===Verb===
{{en-verb|accru}}

# {{label|en|intransitive}} To increase, to [[augment]]; to come to by way of increase; to [[arise]] or spring as a growth or result; to be added as increase, profit, or damage, especially as the [[produce]] of money [[lent]].
#* ''And though power failed, her courage did '''accrue''''' - [[w:Edmund Spenser|Edmund Spenser]]
#* ''Interest '''accrues''' to principal'' - [[Abbott]]
#* ''The great and essential advantages '''accruing''' to society from the freedom of the press'' - [[Junius]]
# {{label|en|intransitive|accounting}} To be [[incurred]] as a result of the passage of time.
#: ''The monthly financial statements show all the actual but only some of the '''accrued''' expenses.''
# {{label|en|intransitive|legal}} To become an enforceable and permanent right.

